history.content: 168 would be ideal, so that's unfortunate. I feel that 61C before 161 will help a lot, but students do often take those courses concurrently. 188 would also be a good choice, and I feel that most 188 professors are great, so you wouldn't be missing out on too much. If you're interested in teaching, 370 could be a good choice here as well on top of perhaps a decal or lab assisting. I'm guessing a breadth or HSS is not an option here. Most other upper divisions would be quite a substantial workload if added to this schedule.

Given that I am declaring at the end of the semester and 168 is really packed up on enrollment what are my next best options for an upper div with EE 120 and CS 61C? Is 161 with Weaver a good second option or not really? I want to take 188 in the Spring with Abbeel so not really considering that one and 170 lecture conflicts with 120 and I've heard that both classes have in class tests
history.subject: Nice course to match with CS 61C + EE 120
